It'd be more consistent with indexing to fix this by having InputRowSerde use a similar construction to IncrementalIndex, rather than by catching ParseExceptions on "innerMap",

``` java
        try {
          agg.aggregate();
        }
        catch (ParseException e) {
          // "aggregate" can throw ParseExceptions if a selector expects something but gets something else.
          if (reportParseExceptions) {
            throw new ParseException(e, "Encountered parse error for aggregator[%s]", agg.getName());
          } else {
            log.debug(e, "Encountered parse error, skipping aggregator[%s].", agg.getName());
          }
        }
